<p><b>VirtualGL</b> is an <a href="/wiki/Open_source" title="Open source">open source</a> program which redirects the 3D rendering commands from <a href="/wiki/Unix" title="Unix">Unix</a> and <a href="/wiki/Linux" title="Linux">Linux</a> <a href="/wiki/OpenGL" title="OpenGL">OpenGL</a> applications to <a href="/wiki/3D_accelerator" title="3D accelerator" class="mw-redirect">3D accelerator</a> hardware in a dedicated server and displays the rendered output interactively to a <a href="/wiki/Thin_client" title="Thin client">thin client</a> located elsewhere on the network.</p>
